Bass off as HSBC rates it a " sell " . Shares in Bass Plc slipped on Monday after analysts at HSBC changed its recommendation for the brewery - to - hotels group from " hold " to " sell " . By 1130 GMT Bass were down 5p at 749p . " Basically we do not see where the growth will come from , " Charles Winston at HSBC said . He would not give any further details at moment , he said . - - London newsroom , + 44 171 542 7717 
